16_4	2.0	In addition to perjury, federal law also prohibits making false statements on federal forms or to federal officers such as FBI agents.
16_5	0.16666666666666666	Unlike perjury, this crime may be committed without a sworn oath.
16_6	2.25	Under federal law, perjury and false statements are punishable by an undetermined fine, up to five years in prison or both.
